---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About | Amid the Noise">
  <section class="section about-hero">
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="about-text">
        <h1>About</h1>
        <p>
          Matthew McClendon is a user experience designer focused on AI-native
          systems that operate under uncertainty.
        </p>
        <p>
          Today’s systems act, infer, and decide. The craft is no longer arranging
          interfaces, but designing the signals, feedback loops, and trust
          mechanisms that make those decisions legible and accountable.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-image-wrap">
        <img
          class="about-image"
          src="/official-profile-1024x.png"
          alt="Matthew McClendon profile portrait"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>What this site is for</h2>
    <p>
      Amid the Noise is where Matthew writes, clarifies, and develops his
      thinking on trust, decision systems, explainability, and human oversight
      in complex environments.
    </p>
    <p>
      The primary audience, at least for now, is recruiters and hiring managers
      looking for strong AI-native UX thinking grounded in systems, judgment,
      and real-world accountability.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>How he works</h2>
    <p>
      Matthew’s work centers on making invisible system behavior visible,
      interpretable, and verifiable. He is especially drawn to products where
      outcomes are probabilistic, stakes are real, and trust has to be designed
      into the experience rather than assumed.
    </p>
    <p>
      His background spans data-intensive platforms, high-stakes workflows, and
      environments where design has to support not just usability, but
      judgment.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <h2>Focus</h2>
    <p>
      AI-native UX design, trust and safety, explainability, human-in-the-loop
      systems, decision workflows, and the design of feedback loops in products
      that no longer wait for input.
    </p>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1fr) 260px;
    gap: 56px;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .about-text {
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .about-image-wrap {
    justify-self: end;
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 260px;
    margin-top: 8px;
  }

  .about-image {
    display: block;
    width: 100%;
    height: auto;
    border: 1px solid var(--line);
    background: var(--bg);
  }

  @media (max-width: 900px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
      gap: 24px;
    }

    .about-image-wrap {
      justify-self: start;
      max-width: 220px;
      margin-top: 0;
    }
  }
</style>